Thanks  for contacting me.
I am Kathrine Solace LLB (Hons) Vice President and CFO
SNR. Partner, Pawlus Life Services Inc.
Hello Helen,
It is with great optimism that I write to you today concerning a 
business transaction that will benefit us both immensely. Actually, I 
contacted you in regards to my deceased client and Realtor Alan Helen 
who was a victim of the train crash that occurred on July 24, 2013 near 
Santiago de Compostela.
Read article:
https://www.theguardian.com/world/santiago-de-compostela-train-crash [1]
http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/picturegalleries/worldnews/10201214/Spain-train-crash-many-dead-as-train-derails-near-Santiago-de-Compostela.html 
[2]
My intention of contacting you is to crave your participation in 
securing the funds deposited by my late client amounting to nine million 
eight hundred thousand Dollar (9,800,000) before his sudden demise. They 
have urged me as his legal attorney to present the beneficiary of the 
said fortune as he didn't mention any beneficiary to them. Since he did 
not know that this would happen, he could not pass on his will.
They have since urged me to present the beneficiary to the funds as the 
funds are prone to being confiscated. All my efforts to contact any of 
his relatives stood futile.
For this reason, I contacted you because you have the same last name as 
my deceased client. To this respect, I ask you for your consent to 
present you to as the beneficiary to the funds.
I will legally apply and obtain all the documents needed to secure the 
funds. All I need is a secure cooperation to enable this transaction. 
You have nothing to worry about as this transaction is 100% risk free. I 
will use my position as the attorney of the deceased to successfully 
carry out this transaction.
The planned transaction will be carried out under an authorized order. 
However, if you wish to reach me with this goal, please contact me for 
further details.
Sincerely,
Kathrine Solace LLB (Hons) Vice President and CFO
Head of Legal Department SNR. Partner
Pawlus Life Services Inc

Canada.
